stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Available : Clipboard Clipboard([String name])

    Available --> Available : String getName()
    Available --> Available : void addFlavorListener([FlavorListener listener])
    Available --> Available : void removeFlavorListener([FlavorListener listener])
    Available --> Available : FlavorListener[] getFlavorListeners()
    Available --> Available : Transferable getContents([Object requestor])
    Available --> Available : DataFlavor[] getAvailableDataFlavors()
    Available --> Available : boolean isDataFlavorAvailable([DataFlavor flavor])
    Available --> Available : Object getData([DataFlavor flavor])
    Available --> Unavailable : void setContents([Transferable contents], [ClipboardOwner owner])

    Unavailable --> Available : void setContents([Transferable contents], [ClipboardOwner owner])
    Unavailable --> Unavailable : String getName()
    Unavailable --> Unavailable : void addFlavorListener([FlavorListener listener])
    Unavailable --> Unavailable : void removeFlavorListener([FlavorListener listener])
    Unavailable --> Unavailable : FlavorListener[] getFlavorListeners()

    note right of Unavailable
        Clipboard is temporarily locked by another application.
        getContents, getAvailableDataFlavors, isDataFlavorAvailable,
        getData, and setContents throw IllegalStateException in this state.
        setContents is modeled as the trigger to re-enter Available once
        the OS releases the clipboard. Transitions are OS-driven externally.
    end note
